This script was written to be run on perlmutter with phenix 1.20.
Instructions on how to run:

1. Setup a folder with all the .cif, .pdb, .mtz files collectively. Make sure that none of them are in subfolders, but all of the files are in one singular folder. 

2. initial_MCR.eff must be in the same folder as well and save the path to this folder.

3. pipeline2.py must be outside this folder. if using different paths to phenix, or you wish to edit the default directory, edit pipeline2.py's main() function and change the relevant strings. 

4. After sourcing phenix version 1.20, run pipeline2.py (with phenix.python pipeline2.py). It will prompt for a directory, in which copy and paste the path. It will prompt for a seed in which you can provide a random number, or just press enter for a random seed.  

